{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1541/comments/5824396.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1541/_/diff#comment-5824396"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1541, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1541.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1541"}}, "title": "Implement configuration (cmake) with MSVC"}, "content": {"raw": "I remember there is a special flag [-DTIXML_USE_STL](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/sdformat/pull-request/100/embed-a-copy-of-tinyxml-for-windows/diff#Lcmake/SearchForStuff.cmakeT40) that is included in Ubuntu as a patch to the header file. In sdformat, we do `add_definitions(-DTIXML_USE_STL)`. I think we should do that here as well?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I remember there is a special flag <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://bitbucket.org/osrf/sdformat/pull-request/100/embed-a-copy-of-tinyxml-for-windows/diff#Lcmake/SearchForStuff.cmakeT40\" rel=\"nofollow\">-DTIXML_USE_STL</a> that is included in Ubuntu as a patch to the header file. In sdformat, we do <code>add_definitions(-DTIXML_USE_STL)</code>. I think we should do that here as well?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-03-23T17:47:51.257452+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": "2015-03-23T17:47:51.266629+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 5824396}